Beginner's Split

Perfect for those just starting their fitness journey

This 3-day split focuses on full-body workouts with adequate rest to build a foundation of strength and proper form. Rest days are essential for recovery and growth.

Day 1: Full Body

  • Squats: 3 sets x 10 reps
  • Push-ups: 3 sets x 10 reps
  • Assisted Pull-ups: 3 sets x 8 reps
  • Planks: 3 sets x 30 seconds

Day 2: Rest

Focus on recovery, stretching, and light cardio if desired.

Day 3: Full Body

  • Lunges: 3 sets x 10 reps per leg
  • Dumbbell Rows: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Shoulder Press: 3 sets x 10 reps
  • Russian Twists: 3 sets x 15 reps per side

Day 4: Rest

Focus on recovery and mobility work.

Day 5: Full Body

  • Goblet Squats: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Incline Push-ups: 3 sets x 12 reps
  • Lat Pulldowns: 3 sets x 10 reps
  • Bicycle Crunches: 3 sets x 20 reps

Days 6-7: Rest

Weekend rest to recover fully. Light walking or yoga is beneficial.

); }; export default BeginnerSplit;
